eric.  My point on the 25k was that I did not even make back what I spent on the spell.  And I am sorry to let you in on this little secret : Everquest is not a universal philanthropic experiment.  I appreciate your opinion, and even empathize as I myself have often wondered why we dont do more sharing.  But the fact is I want to see and do places like Vex Thal and Hall of Honor.  And the fact is to do these places you need gear that rocks and to get to the places that drops the no drop gear that rocks you need to buy gear that will let you live in those places.  Get off your high horse buddy, oh wait, you cannot afford one.  Ummmm get off your soapbox and go enjoy the game for what it is... a microcosim of the real world.  If you want to roleplay a social worker.. Super <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , every community needs one. Be a guide or some other help intensive, thank you based reward character.  I cannot believe you would fault a character for taking advantage of their abilities - I can only assume you are insane with jealously.<br>
<br>
As far as casting KEI on a raid, well maybe your server is just filled with enchanters tired of dealing with sniveling little gimme whiners like yourself.  I myself do free KEI's for CR's, and of course if 'I' am on the raid I KEI the whole raid.  I am sure we are missing part of the story when it comes to your mysterious unKEIing ench.  <br>
<br>
Also, 900 mana is a damn big chunk of the mana pool.  So if you come across an enchanter in the field and he doesnt throw KEI on you just cuz dont be suprised, enchanters need that mana to keep groups alive. <br>
<br>
As far as clerics being better - - - - well every class is needed, no doubt.  But I have been in plenty of higher end groups and often have no cleric.  Not that I dont think they are needed, not bashing clerics or any other class so dont go running with that thread or I will just delete my post.  I am just amazed that you have played the game this long and are still crying. <br>
<br>
Also, my point on the 25k was only that I planned on taking donations till I recovered my 34k.  But, so many people refused to donate after i had cast that i just gave up on it altogether.  I made my character from scratch, and dont owe anyone jack, so dont tell me how i am obligated to dump kei on you just because it is componentless.  Gotta go now i feel my blueberry waffles coming back up.<br>
